# .templatesyncignore
# Paths listed here are NEVER overwritten when syncing updates from the
# bc-alm-template repository (used by .github/workflows/template-sync.yml and
# by scripts/Update-FromTemplate.ps1). These are "project-owned" files: your
# real code and the values written by the one-time initializer.
#
# Everything NOT listed here is "template-managed" and will be updated from the
# template (agents, skills, instructions, scripts, meta-docs, workflows).
# Syntax is .gitignore-style.

# --- Your AL source (the sample app is only a starting point) ---
app/
test/

# --- One-time initializer output / configured values ---
template.config.json
PROJECT.md
.github/copilot-instructions.md
.vscode/launch.json
.vscode/mcp.json
.vscode/settings.json
*.code-workspace

# --- Your specs (keep the blank template, ignore real specs) ---
specs/*
!specs/_TEMPLATE/
!specs/_TEMPLATE/**

# --- Repo identity / meta you own ---
README.md
LICENSE
.git*

# --- The sync workflow keeps updating itself; that's intentional, so it is
#     NOT ignored. Remove the leading '#' below if you want to pin your own copy.
# .github/workflows/template-sync.yml
